meanings.english_definition: A surname of Irish origin, anglicized from Ó hÉinín.

meanings.definition: Bobby "The Brain" Heenan (1944–2017), an American professional wrestling manager, commentator, and wrestler.
meanings.english_definition: Bobby "The Brain" Heenan (1944–2017), an American professional wrestling manager, commentator, and wrestler.
examples: Bobby Heenan was known for his witty commentary and managing skills.

etymology.value: Anglicized form of the Irish surname Ó hÉinín, meaning "descendant of Éinín". Éinín is a personal name derived from éan, meaning "bird".
